CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 31, 1962, pg. A3 reads: With "The Grand" - With Grand Daughter Ruler Nettie Smith seated at his right, Grand Exalted Ruler Hobson Reynolds of the Improved, Benevolent and Protective Order of Elks of the World is shown surrounded by Elks' dignitaries at the recent ball held in the Penn-Sheraton. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Grand Exalted Ruler Hobson Reynolds wearing chain collar and fez, seated at banquet table next to Grand Daughter Ruler Nettie Smith on right, surrounded by group of men and women in Penn Sheraton for Elks Ball
